extends layout 

block content
    .container 
        h2.pageTitle Set Up
        .container
        br
        p Welcome to the Set Up page, on this page you will find how to use Phenoflow on your computer depending on your operating system.
        p If you find any difficulties using Phenoflow, don't hesitate to ask us questions through the <a href = '/contactUs' class ="contactUsLink" > contact us</a> page.
        hr
        h3 Mac-OS
        hr
        br
        h5 1. Install the prequesites
        .setUpTable
            table.table.table-sm
                    thead
                        tr
                        th(scope='col') Step
                        th(scope='col') What to do ? 
                        th(scope='col') Check
                    tbody
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 1.1
                            td Open the terminal (You can find it your computer applications) </a>
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 1.2
                            td Install docker using this <a href =https://docs.docker.com/desktop/mac/install/ class ="contactUsLink"> link </a> and follow the instructions provided by Docker website.
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 1.3
                            td Install CWLTool using this <a href =https://github.com/common-workflow-language/cwltool#install class ="contactUsLink"> link </a> and follow the instructions on the website.
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        

        br
        h5 2. Find a phenotype to test.
        .setUpTable
            table.table.table-sm
                    thead
                        tr
                        th(scope='col') Step
                        th(scope='col') What to do ? 
                        th(scope='col') Check
                    tbody
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 2.1
                            td Click on "Browse" icon on the navbar and search for a specific phenotype to test
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 2.2
                            td Download the phenotype
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 2.3
                            td Place the phenotype folder in a specific location (Optional)
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">

        br
        h5 3. Test the phenotype 
        .setUpTable
            table.table.table-sm
                    thead
                        tr
                        th(scope='col') Step
                        th(scope='col') What to do ? 
                        th(scope='col') Check
                    tbody
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 3.1
                            td Replace the "replaceMe.csv" with your dataset (must be a CSV file). If you don't know how how to create a data set for your phenotype. Check this <a href ="/" class ="contactUsLink"> link </a>
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 3.2
                            td Open [Phenotype name]-inputs.yml (e.g : If my phenotype is "Acne" the file will be called Acne-inputs.yml) with a text editor (e.g : Atom)
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                        tr
                            th(scope='row') 3.3
                            td Change the potentialCases path with your CSV data file name. (Don't forget to write .csv at the end of your file name)
                            td <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" class="custom-checkbox" id="flexCheckDefault">
                            
        br    
        h6 Note: Step 3.2 and 3.3 are optionals if you name your dataset input "replaceMe.csv" as the old file
        br
        br
